*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪsən|Rhymes: -ɪsən]]

=== Verb ===
{{en-verb}}
# {{intransitive}} To pay [[attention]] to, to [[note]].
#: ''Please '''listen''' carefully to what I am about to say.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[wait]] for a [[sound]] as a [[signal]].
#: ''You should '''listen''' for the starting gun.''
# To [[obey]] [[oral]] instruction.
#: ''Good children '''listen''' to their parents.''
# {{rfv-sense}} To have a [[chat]] with someone, particularly a confidential one.

====Quotations====
*'''1855''' — [[w:Henry Wadsworth Longfellow|Henry Wadsworth Longfellow]], ''[[s:The Song of Hiawatha|The Song of Hiawatha]]'', introduction
*:Ye who love a nation’s legends,<br/>Love the ballads of a people,<br/>That like voices from afar off<br/>Call to us to pause and '''listen'''

